ZH: 我不喝酒。
EN: I don't drink alcohol.

ZH: 他很能喝酒。
EN: He can handle his alcohol well.

ZH: 周末的时候，我喜欢喝一杯红酒。
EN: I enjoy a glass of red wine on the weekends.

ZH: 喝酒不要喝得太多。
EN: Don't drink too much alcohol.

ZH: 他很会选好酒。
EN: He knows how to pick good wine.

ZH: 在庆祝的时候，我们都喜欢喝一杯香槟。
EN: We all enjoy a glass of champagne when celebrating.

ZH: 喝酒过量对身体不好。
EN: Excessive drinking is bad for your health.

ZH: 我对白酒没什么兴趣。
EN: I'm not interested in baijiu.

ZH: 在中国，喝茶和喝酒都是一种社交活动。
EN: In China, drinking tea and alcohol are both social activities.

ZH: 他喜欢喝冰酒。
EN: He likes to drink ice wine.

ZH: 面对困难时，他常常靠喝酒来解压。
EN: When faced with difficulties, he often relies on alcohol to relieve stress.

ZH: 过节的时候，我们都会喝一些梅酒。
EN: We drink plum wine during festivals.

ZH: 喝酒会影响驾驶能力。
EN: Drinking alcohol can impair your driving.

ZH: 他喜欢喝一杯白兰地。
EN: He enjoys a glass of brandy.

ZH: 周末晚上，我喜欢在家里喝一些啤酒。
EN: I like to have some beer at home on weekend nights.

ZH: 他喝了一瓶啤酒，就开始变得疯疯癫癫的。
EN: He started acting crazy after finishing a bottle of beer.

ZH: 喝酒过头会让你后悔不已。
EN: Drinking too much alcohol will make you regret it.

ZH: 你不会喝醉了吧？
EN: You're not drunk, are you?

ZH: 他拒绝喝酒。
EN: He refuses to drink alcohol.
